      <h2 class="section__title">Trivandrum Python Community Code of Conduct</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="content-page__body">
      <p>The <a href="https://policies.python.org/python.org/code-of-conduct/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Python Software Foundation Code of Conduct</a> applies to all online and offline events, communications, and interactions related to Trivandrum Python Community.</p>

      <h3 class="content-page__subheading">Anti-Harassment and Anti-Bullying Policy</h3>

      <p>Trivandrum Python Community is dedicated to providing a respectful, harassment-free community for everyone. We do not tolerate harassment or bullying of any community member in any form. This does not only extend to members of the Trivandrum Python Community, but to anyone who chooses to become involved in the larger Trivandrum Python Community of users, developers and integrators through events or interactions.</p>

      <p>Harassment includes offensive verbal/electronic comments related to personal characteristics or choices, sexual images or comments in public or online spaces, deliberate intimidation, bullying, stalking, following, harassing photography or recording, sustained disruption of talks, IRC chats, electronic meetings, physical meetings or other events, inappropriate physical contact, or unwelcome sexual attention. Participants asked to stop any harassing or bullying behavior are expected to comply immediately.</p>

      <p>If a participant engages in harassing behavior, representatives of the community may take reasonable action they deem appropriate, including warning the offender, expulsion from any Trivandrum Python Community event, or expulsion from mailing lists, IRC chats, discussion boards and other electronic communications channels to resolve the issue. This may include expulsion from Trivandrum Python Community membership.</p>

      <p>If you are being harassed, notice that someone else is being harassed, or have any other concerns, please act to intercede or ask for help from any member of the Trivandrum Python Community, IRC chat admins, website admins, or organizers/representatives of any physical events put on under the auspices of the Trivandrum Python Community.</p>

      <p class="content-page__attribution">The anti-harassment policy has been adapted from the <a href="https://plone.org/foundation/about" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Plone Foundation</a> and is licensed under a <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Creative Commons Attribution-Share Alike 3.0 Unported license</a>.</p>
